 1370","1366":"1366","1322":"1322","1387":"from 9 January 1387 to 8 January 1388","1331":"1331","1419":"1419","1406":"1406","1329":"1329","Walton-le-Dale, Lancashire, England":"Walton-le-Dale, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England","Gwynedd, Wales":"Gwynedd, Wales, United Kingdom","Kinderton, Cheshire, England":"Kinderton, Cheshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Langton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from one or more of the many places called with Old English <i>lang</i> ‘long’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’, such as Langton Hall in Kirkby in Ashfield (Nottinghamshire), Langton Lodge in Hendon (Middlesex), Langton (Yorkshire), East and West Langton (Leicestershire), Langton by Horncastle, Langton by Spilsby, and Langton by Wragby (all in Lincolnshire), and Lanton (Northumb). Compare   Lankton  ,   Lanton  , and   Longton  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Lanton","meanings":["English: variant of   Langton  ."]},{"name":"Lankton","meanings":["English: variant of   Langton  .","History: Thomas Lankton, born <i>c.</i> 1714 in Hartford County, CT, died 1783 in Litchfield County, CT, was a son of Joseph Langton."]},{"name":"Longton","meanings":["habitational name from Longton in Lancashire. The placename derives from Old English <i>lang</i> ‘long’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’.","variant of   Langton  .","English:"]}]},{"name":"Ralph","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Norman French name, <i>Raulf</i>, a contracted form of the Germanic personal name <i>Radulf</i>, derived from <i>rād</i> ‘counsel’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’. The spelling with <i>-ph</i> is due to classical influence in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Ralf","meanings":["From a Norman French name, <i>Raulf</i>, a contracted form of the Germanic personal name <i>Radulf</i>, derived from <i>rād</i> ‘counsel’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’. The spelling with <i>-ph</i> is due to classical influence in the 18th century."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ralph de Langton was born in 1340, in Walton-le-Dale, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, his father, John de Langton of Walton-Le-Dale, was 18 and his mother, Mrs. John de Langton, was 19. He married Joan Radcliffe about 1370. They were the parents of at least 4 sons and 1 daughter. He died in 1406, in his hometown, at the age of 66."},"et":{"1340–1406":"1340–1406","1329–Male":"1329–Surnud","1331–Male":"1331–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1340–1425":"1340–1425","1363–1450":"1363–1450","1366–1419":"1366–1419","1322–1360":"1322–1360","1322–1387":"1322–9.jaanuar1387kuni8.jaanuar1388","1363":"1363","1340":"1340","1450":"1450","1360":"1360","1425":"1425","Abt 1370":"umbes 1370","1366":"1366","1322":"1322","1387":"9. jaanuar 1387 kuni 8. jaanuar 1388","1331":"1331","1419":"1419","1406":"1406","1329":"1329","Walton-le-Dale, Lancashire, England":"Walton-le-Dale, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Gwynedd, Wales":"Gwynedd, Wales, United Kingdom","Kinderton, Cheshire, England":"Kinderton, Cheshire, England"},"fi":{"1340–1406":"1340–1406","1329–Male":"1329–Kuollut","1331–Male":"1331–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1340–1425":"1340–1425","